</taxonomicName>
in the Palearctic 
<collectingRegion id="49BD69A0FF82FF99F53DFE3EEA4EFE55" box="[1067,1150,404,430]" country="Iraq" pageId="7" pageNumber="394">Region</collectingRegion>
(Yu et al., 2012).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC6A742FF82FF99F1F5FE7FECBAFD14" blockId="7.[174,1233,404,1007]" pageId="7" pageNumber="394">
С o m p a r a t i v e n o t e s. 
<taxonomicName id="4C79DCC1FF82FF99F30DFE7FECB9FE15" baseAuthorityName="Nees" baseAuthorityYear="1834" box="[539,649,469,494]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Paralipsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="394" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="enervis">
<emphasis id="B90D7B50FF82FF99F30DFE7FECB9FE15" box="[539,649,469,494]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="394">P. enervis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="1342BBC7FF82FF99F38EFE7EED3BFE14" box="[664,779,468,495]" captionStart-0="Fig" captionStart-1="Fig" captionStart-2="Fig" captionStart-3="Fig" captionStart-4="Fig" captionStart-5="Fig" captionStart-6="Fig" captionStartId-0="6.[170,202,1708,1730]" captionStartId-1="1.[178,211,875,897]" captionStartId-2="2.[168,201,1145,1167]" captionStartId-3="3.[174,207,1718,1740]" captionStartId-4="4.[166,199,1722,1744]" captionStartId-5="5.[171,204,1732,1754]" captionStartId-6="7.[174,205,1723,1745]" captionTargetBox-0="[296,1099,565,1690]" captionTargetBox-1="[273,1126,188,832]" captionTargetBox-2="[258,1095,178,1094]" captionTargetBox-3="[263,1124,733,1688]" captionTargetBox-4="[275,1082,1029,1703]" captionTargetBox-5="[321,1089,843,1706]" captionTargetBox-6="[534,881,1072,1704]" captionTargetId-0="figure-130@6.[288,1111,557,1687]" captionTargetId-1="figure-316@1.[254,1139,174,852]" captionTargetId-2="figure-247@2.[235,1130,166,1111]" captionTargetId-3="figure-5@3.[237,1132,714,1714]" captionTargetId-4="figure-329@4.[256,1104,1015,1723]" captionTargetId-5="figure-5@5.[311,1097,833,1721]" captionTargetId-6="figure-347@7.[529,894,1061,1710]" captionTargetPageId-1="1" captionTargetPageId-2="2" captionTargetPageId-3="3" captionTargetPageId-4="4" captionTargetPageId-5="5" captionTargetPageId-6="7" captionText-0="Fig.6. Paralipsis enervis, ♀ (1–7) and Protaphidius wissmannii,♀ (9–12, 14), Ơ (8, 13): 1, 8 — habitus; 2, 9 — head, lateral aspect; 3, 10 — antenna; 4, 11 — forewing; 5, 12 — propodeum; 6, 13 — petiole; 7, 14 — ovipositor sheath. Рис. 6. Paralipsis enervis, ♀ (1–7) и Protaphidius wissmannii, ♀ (9–12, 14), Ơ (8, 13): 1, 8 — габитус; 2, 9 — голова, вид сбоку; 3, 10 — усик; 4, 11 — переднее крыло; 5, 12 — проподеум; 6, 13 — стебелёк; 7, 14 — створки яйцеклада." captionText-1="Fig. 1. Adialytus salicaphis, ♀ (1–5) and A. ambiguus, ♀ (6–10): 1, 6 — antenna; 2, 7 — forewing; 3, 8 — propodeum; 4, 9 — petiole; 5, 10 — ovipositor sheath. Рис. 1. Adialytus salicaphis, ♀ (1–5) и A. ambiguus, ♀ (6–10): 1, 6 — усик; 2, 7 — переднее крыло; 3, 8 — проподеум; 4, 9 — стебелёк; 5, 10 — створки яйцеклада." captionText-2="Fig. 2. Aphidius megourae, ♀ (1–6) and A. funebris, ♀ (7–12): 1, 7 — head, dorsal aspect; 2, 8 — antenna; 3, 9 — forewing; 4, 10 — propodeum; 5, 11 — petiole; 6, 12 — ovipositor sheath. Рис. 2. Aphidius megourae, ♀ (1–6) и A. funebris, ♀ (7–12): 1, 7 — голова, вид сверху; 2, 8 — усик; 3, 9 — переднее крыло; 4, 10 — проподеум; 5, 11 — стебелёк; 6, 12 — створки яйцеклада." captionText-3="Fig. 3. Areopraon silvestre, ♀ (1–6) and Praon volucre, ♀ (7–12): 1, 7 — antenna; 2, 8 — mesonotum; 3, 9 — forewing; 4, 10 — propodeum; 5, 11 — petiole; 6, 12 — ovipositor sheath. Рис. 3. Areopraon silvestre, ♀ (1–6) и Praon volucre, ♀ (7–12): 1, 7 — усик; 2, 8 — среднеспинка; 3, 9 — переднее крыло; 4, 10 — проподеум; 5, 11 — стебелёк; 6, 12 — створки яйцеклада." captionText-4="Fig. 4. Diaeretus leucopterus, ♀ (1–5) and Diaeretiella rapae, ♀ (6–10): 1, 6 — antenna; 2, 7 — forewing; 3, 8 — propodeum; 4, 9 — petiole; 5, 10 — ovipositor sheath (5 — after Takada, 1968). Рис. 4. Diaeretus leucopterus, ♀ (1–5) и Diaeretiella rapae, ♀ (6–10): 1, 6 — усик; 2, 7 — переднее крыло; 3, 8 — проподеум; 4, 9 — стебелёк; 5, 10 — створки яйцеклада (5 — по: Takada, 1968)." captionText-5="Fig. 5. Ephedrus cerasicola, ♀ (1–6), E.plagiator, ♀ (7, 10–12), E. niger, ♀ (8, 9): 1, 7 — antenna; 2, 8 — mesonotum; 3, 9 — forewing; 4, 10 — propodeum; 5, 11 — petiole; 6, 12 — ovipositor sheath. Рис. 5. Ephedrus cerasicola, ♀ (1–6), E. plagiator, ♀ (7, 10–12), E. niger, ♀ (8, 9): 1, 7 — усик; 2, 8 — среднеспинка; 3, 9 — переднее крыло; 4, 10 — проподеум; 5, 11 — стебелёк; 6, 12 — створки яйцеклада." captionText-6="Fig.7. Pauesia abietis, ♀: 1 — antenna; 2 — mesonotum; 3 — forewing; 4 — propodeum; 5 — petiole; 6 — ovipositor sheath. Рис. 7. Pauesia abietis, ♀: 1 — усик; 2 — среднеспинка; 3 — переднее крыло; 4 — проподеум; 5 — стебелёк; 6 — створки яйцеклада." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6467466" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6467454" figureDoi-2="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6449135" figureDoi-3="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6467456" figureDoi-4="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6467460" figureDoi-5="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6467462" figureDoi-6="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6449137" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/6467466/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/6467454/files/figure.png" httpUri-2="https://zenodo.org/record/6449135/files/figure.png" httpUri-3="https://zenodo.org/record/6467456/files/figure.png" httpUri-4="https://zenodo.org/record/6467460/files/figure.png" httpUri-5="https://zenodo.org/record/6467462/files/figure.png" httpUri-6="https://zenodo.org/record/6449137/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="394">
fig. 6, 
<emphasis id="B90D7B50FF82FF99F3F6FE7FED3BFE14" box="[736,779,469,495]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="394">1–7</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
) may be confused in habitus with 
<taxonomicName id="4C79DCC1FF82FF99F588FE7FEC16FDF5" authority="Ratzeburg" authorityName="Ratzeburg" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Protaphidius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="394" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wissmannii">
<emphasis id="B90D7B50FF82FF99F588FE7FEF96FDF5" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="394">Protaphidius wissmannii</emphasis>
Ratzeburg
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="1342BBC7FF82FF99F323FE5EEC43FDF5" box="[565,627,500,526]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="6.[170,202,1708,1730]" captionTargetBox="[296,1099,565,1690]" captionTargetId="figure-130@6.[288,1111,557,1687]" captionText="Fig.6. Paralipsis enervis, ♀ (1–7) and Protaphidius wissmannii,♀ (9–12, 14), Ơ (8, 13): 1, 8 — habitus; 2, 9 — head, lateral aspect; 3, 10 — antenna; 4, 11 — forewing; 5, 12 — propodeum; 6, 13 — petiole; 7, 14 — ovipositor sheath. Рис. 6. Paralipsis enervis, ♀ (1–7) и Protaphidius wissmannii, ♀ (9–12, 14), Ơ (8, 13): 1, 8 — габитус; 2, 9 — голова, вид сбоку; 3, 10 — усик; 4, 11 — переднее крыло; 5, 12 — проподеум; 6, 13 — стебелёк; 7, 14 — створки яйцеклада." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6467466" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6467466/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="394">fig. 6</figureCitation>
, 
<emphasis id="B90D7B50FF82FF99F369FE5FEC88FDF4" box="[639,696,501,527]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="394">8–14</emphasis>
) (particularly with males): both species share long and apically dilated scapus, filiform near to moniliform antenna, strongly sclerotized stigma, heavyset body, oval apex of the abdomen (
<taxonomicName id="4C79DCC1FF82FF99F3E9FD9FED9CFDB5" box="[767,940,565,590]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Protaphidius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="394" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wissmannii">
<emphasis id="B90D7B50FF82FF99F3E9FD9FED9CFDB5" box="[767,940,565,590]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="394">Pr. wissmannii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
males), 
<taxonomicName id="4C79DCC1FF82FF99F506FD9FEA4FFDB5" baseAuthorityName="Nees" baseAuthorityYear="1834" box="[1040,1151,565,590]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Paralipsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="394" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="enervis">
<emphasis id="B90D7B50FF82FF99F506FD9FEA4FFDB5" box="[1040,1151,565,590]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="394">P. enervis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C79DCC1FF82FF99F1F9FDFFEFABFD95" box="[239,411,597,622]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Protaphidius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="394" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wissmannii">
<emphasis id="B90D7B50FF82FF99F1F9FDFFEFABFD95" box="[239,411,597,622]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="394">Pr. wissmannii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by: 1) smaller eyes; 2) very long scapus, that is notably longer than F1; 3) antenna with only 15–16 segments; 4) another 
<typeStatus id="54C219E0FF82FF99F3E7FDDFED13FD74" box="[753,803,629,655]" pageId="7" pageNumber="394">type</typeStatus>
of forewing venation: no central cell and almost no metacarpus, radial vein is very short, and looks like a point; 5) propodeum without areolae or carinae; 6) short petiole; 7) abdomen with normally developed tergites; 8) ovipositor sheath thinned to the apex.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C363F4C9FF82FF99F1F5FD5FECEBFC14" pageId="7" pageNumber="394" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="8BC6A742FF82FF99F1F5FD5FECD3FC74" blockId="7.[174,1233,404,1007]" pageId="7" pageNumber="394">
H o s t s. 
<taxonomicName id="4C79DCC1FF82FF99F05CFD5FEFDFFCF5" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1775" box="[330,495,757,783]" class="Insecta" family="Aphididae" genus="Anoecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="394" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="corni">
<emphasis id="B90D7B50FF82FF99F05CFD5FEFDFFCF5" box="[330,495,757,783]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="394">Anoecia corni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C79DCC1FF82FF99F317FD5FECBBFCF5" box="[513,651,757,783]" class="Insecta" family="Aphididae" genus="Anoecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="394" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B90D7B50FF82FF99F317FD5FEC6FFCF4" box="[513,607,757,783]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="394">Anoecia</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
; 
<emphasis id="B90D7B50FF82FF99F38BFD5EEAF9FCF5" box="[669,1225,756,783]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="394">
